column1: SIT2 | Telesales |Z_PRT00129982A | Couldn’t see LegacyCustomerID present in submit order request
column30:
I tried running one Telesales Mobile New ACQ flow in SIT2 but couldn’t see LegacyCustomerID present in submit order request.

Could you please check?

PFA logs for your reference.

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

 
 # Login to Telesales channel
 # Select Mobile Package
 # Move to checkout
 # Fill customer details
 # Submit the Order

 

*Expected Result:*

Submit order request should contain LegacyCustomerID.

 

*Actual Result:*

Couldn’t see LegacyCustomerID present in submit order request. It’s empty

 

<Customer>

<LegacyCustomerID/>

<SourceCustomerID>1</SourceCustomerID>

<LineOfBusiness>Mobile_Postpaid</LineOfBusiness>

<Type>PRIVATE</Type>

<CustomerPassword>DEMO1</CustomerPassword>
column700:
11/Sep/23 5:43 PM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~sudhanshu.shekhar@vodafone.com] 

 

Hi Sudhanshu,

 
h3. {color:#172b4d}Nandkumar Gaikwad {color}
added a comment -

 
 
 * LegacyCustomerID is populated only in case of any sales flow for an existing customer. Please find the reference document that mentioned the condition for LegacyCustomerID.

!02d7aa7e-5678-49b1-892d-e5add93f1115.png!
|LegacyCustomerID|String|O| |The customer ID from the back-end, in case the customer already exists. *For New customers, the field will be empty*|;;;

column1: SIT1 | Retail | Component type Insurance is not there in SubmitOrder Request
column30:
Hello Omnius Team,

I tried running one Retail mobile New Flow in SIT3, order was successful also but couldn’t see component type as Insurance in SubmitOrder request.

Could you please check?

PFA logs for your reference.
column700:
10/Apr/23 9:15 AM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~sudhanshu.shekhar@vodafone.com] 

 
Shifali Guleria added a comment -
 
 
In Submit Order Request we are sending only 
*IMEI* - DATA/OrderLineList/OrderLine/SystemAdditionalData[AttributeCode=’IMEI’]/AttributeValue
*DeviceColour* - DATA/OrderLineList/OrderLine/SystemAdditionalData[AttributeCode=’DeviceColour’]/AttributeValue

Both IMEI and DeviceColour are present in the SubmitOrder logs (GenerateContract and FulFillment mode) shared by you.;;;
column702: 10/Apr/23 10:47 AM;sudhanshu.shekhar@vodafone.com;Omnius team will check and analyze this issue on priority and if required they will check with their BA;;;
column703:
11/Apr/23 11:49 AM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~sudhanshu.shekhar@vodafone.com] 

 
Shifali Guleria added a comment -
 
This defect is a PCAT issue.
The value *ComponentType* we get from PCAT and the same value for the added Insurance Product is then added in submit Order logs.;;;
column704: 11/Apr/23 1:50 PM;sudhanshu.shekhar@vodafone.com;Thomas Wermke, Vodafone (External) is checking this issue;;;
column705: 11/Apr/23 4:45 PM;thomas.wermke@vodafone.com;Currently in PAPS Multimapper rules are enhanced with SQL ([OS-4377 Add ComponentType "HIS" for Handset Insurance SOCs|https://osf-telesales-int-acc1.vodafone.de:8043/opm-gui/sqledit?371-1.ILinkListener-tabs-panel-sqlTable-wrapper-body-tableBorder-tableBorder_body-table-body-rows-18-cells-1-cell-link]) for all SKUs/KIAS-SOCs having SOC.EXTRA_HANDLE_IND=HIS and which have a contract_type in KIAS. For those SKUs the component type 'HIS' is added. As the new handset insurance special SOCs CO3SD1080, CO3SD1100, CO3SD1120 and CO3SD1140 are not setup in KIAS as contract SOCs, the SQL-script in PAPS needs to be enhanced accordingly to add the component type 'HIS' also for SKUs being part of the new category 'Mobile->VODAFONE_COVER_PLUS'.;;;
column707: 12/Apr/23 1:49 PM;pallavi.chaudhari1@vodafone.com;latest PCAT  is received PCAT coping in progress from SB1 to SIT1;;;
column708: 12/Apr/23 2:06 PM;horst.froehlich@vodafone.com;Please start re-test right PCAT copy from SB1 to SIT1 is finalized.;;;
column709:
13/Apr/23 12:51 PM;sudhanshu.shekhar@vodafone.com;As we had discussed either Insurance or HIS should be part of Component type in SubmitOrder request.

I found below thing after retesting it.

 <ComponentType>FeatureService|HIS</ComponentType>
 <AdditionalValue>HIS</AdditionalValue>
<ComponentType>FeatureService|HIS</ComponentType>

OGW team is verifying if this is what they are expecting.;;;
column710:

OGW expects this component type as below.

Can you please check with Omnius why we are getting it in different format than below.

<ComponentType>HIS</ComponentType>

Or

<ComponentType>Insurance</ComponentType>;;;

And it was running fine with the address Am Seestern 430 40547 Düsseldorf .

Issue happens only if tester is using his own Mocks, with below fake data:
 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 
And this issue happens because we don't have any Bandwidth 250 definition for IP Bitsteam, see also "CRFN200 ILS: Technology IP-Bitstream obligated" . So some years ago, as IP Bitsream goes life, the maximum bandwidth of it was 100 Mbits, till now we didn't get any change request to enhance it with higher bandwidth.

So the issue mentioned on this ticket is actually not an error. In case you want to enhance the IP-Bitstream with bandwith 250 Mbits, Let's talk to Business OnDemand Team at first.

column706:
06/Mar/23 9:33 AM;bhuvi.chowdhary@vodafone.com;Dear All,

 

As we all know that since last week 21{^}st{^} Feb 2023 – until 28{^}th{^} Feb 2023—we had a Critical issue which blocked both SIT/ACC env –where we were facing OILàOGW timeouts due to which everything in testing was blocked.

 

Finally, after a lot of  investigations, analysis and checks –we identified the Root cause of the issue, which now has been fixed and now we aren’t getting any timeout issue on the envs.

 

Just to summarize – please do find the below RCA of the issue:-

 

{*}+Issue+{*}:- Timeout problems while connecting OILàOGW

 

*+Impact+* : All SIT/ACC Testing Env execution were blocked—Impacted SIT deliveries, Regression testing delay, Production build release delays

 

{*}+Issue occurrence reason+{*}: There was an upgrade done on the Kafka Linux servers on 20{^}th{^} Feb 2023(10PM CET) –where during upgrade all the 3 Broker nodes were also by default updated. Post upgrade by unknown reason #1 nodes Java Jdk version was upgraded to higher version than the other 2 nodes.—due to which when request was triggered to this #1 node—SSL handshake issues were encountered.

 

*+Resolution for fix:-+* #1 nodes Java JDK version was downgraded and broker node restarted.

 ;;;
column707:
06/Mar/23 9:34 AM;bhuvi.chowdhary@vodafone.com;one small correction:

 

where during upgrade all the 3 Broker nodes were also by default updated

Only 1 broker was patched not all – which causes inaccessibility of this broker.

The other 2 are NOT patched or updated.

 

BR, ALEX

 ;;;

column1: SIT1 | Telesales | Getting 504 Gateway timeout error
column30:
Steps to reproduce the issue:
 # Login to SIT1 ENV Telesales channel
 # Perform Mobile postpaid ACQ flow for SOHO customer
 # Select HW and Tariff and added into the shopping cart
 # Select Multisim option(Vodafone One Number) and choose E-Sim
 # Select Online Ident method at customer details section
 # Fill all the mandatory details and continue 
 # Create contract summary
 # Click on Submit order button on Voice log page
 # Verify the Order View page

27/Feb/23 10:08 AM;bhuvi.chowdhary@vodafone.com;Hi Piyush,

 

I had a call with Ahmed, and we corrected the file. There is a logic on EAI for picking the file and sending it in response. Based on soap header input value of boid, EAI simulator picks the file and process the response. So, the file name should be in sync with boid otherwise you will get a default response.

 

Regards,

Nithiyanandam;;;
